The paper is about resource allocation in cognitive radio networks, which is a subfield of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The proposed strategy is based on deep neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the training method for the neural networks, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY).
